{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Hello. My name is Birke Baehr,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and I'm 11 years old."},{"time":5000,"text":"I came here today to talk about what's wrong with our food system."},{"time":8000,"text":"First of all, I would like to say"},{"time":10000,"text":"that I'm really amazed at how easily kids are led to believe"},{"time":13000,"text":"all the marketing and advertising"},{"time":15000,"text":"on TV, at public schools"},{"time":17000,"text":"and pretty much everywhere else you look."},{"time":19000,"text":"It seems to me like corporations"},{"time":21000,"text":"are always trying to get kids, like me,"},{"time":23000,"text":"to get their parents to buy stuff"},{"time":25000,"text":"that really isn't good for us or the planet."},{"time":27000,"text":"Little kids, especially,"},{"time":29000,"text":"are attracted by colorful packaging"},{"time":31000,"text":"and plastic toys."},{"time":33000,"text":"I must admit, I used to be one of them."},{"time":36000,"text":"I also used to think that all of our food"},{"time":38000,"text":"came from these happy, little farms"},{"time":40000,"text":"where pigs rolled in mud and cows grazed on grass all day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"What I discovered was this is not true."},{"time":46000,"text":"I began to look into this stuff"},{"time":48000,"text":"on the Internet, in books and in documentary films,"},{"time":51000,"text":"in my travels with my family."},{"time":53000,"text":"I discovered the dark side of the industrialized food system."},{"time":57000,"text":"First, there's genetically engineered seeds and organisms."},{"time":60000,"text":"That is when a seed is manipulated in a laboratory"},{"time":63000,"text":"to do something not intended by nature --"},{"time":65000,"text":"like taking the DNA of a fish"},{"time":67000,"text":"and putting it into the DNA of a tomato. Yuck."},{"time":70000,"text":"Don't get me wrong, I like fish and tomatoes,"},{"time":73000,"text":"but this is just creepy."},{"time":75000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":77000,"text":"The seeds are then planted, then grown."},{"time":79000,"text":"The food they produce have been proven"},{"time":81000,"text":"to cause cancer and other problems in lab animals,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and people have been eating food produced this way"},{"time":85000,"text":"since the 1990s."},{"time":87000,"text":"And most folks don't even know they exist."},{"time":89000,"text":"Did you know rats that ate genetically engineered corn"},{"time":92000,"text":"had developed signs of liver and kidney toxicity?"},{"time":95000,"text":"These include kidney inflammation and lesions and increased kidney weight."},{"time":98000,"text":"Yet almost all the corn we eat"},{"time":100000,"text":"has been altered genetically in some way."},{"time":102000,"text":"And let me tell you,"},{"time":104000,"text":"corn is in everything."},{"time":106000,"text":"And don't even get me started on the Confined Animal Feeding Operations"},{"time":108000,"text":"called CAFOS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"Conventional farmers use chemical fertilizers"},{"time":114000,"text":"made from fossil fuels"},{"time":116000,"text":"that they mix with the dirt to make plants grow."},{"time":118000,"text":"They do this because they've stripped the soil from all nutrients"},{"time":121000,"text":"from growing the same crop over and over again."},{"time":124000,"text":"Next, more harmful chemicals are sprayed on fruits and vegetables,"},{"time":127000,"text":"like pesticides and herbicides,"},{"time":129000,"text":"to kill weeds and bugs."},{"time":131000,"text":"When it rains, these chemicals seep into the ground,"},{"time":134000,"text":"or run off into our waterways,"},{"time":136000,"text":"poisoning our water too."},{"time":138000,"text":"Then they irradiate our food, trying to make it last longer,"},{"time":141000,"text":"so it can travel thousands of miles"},{"time":143000,"text":"from where it's grown to the supermarkets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146000,"text":"So I ask myself,"},{"time":148000,"text":"how can I change? How can I change these things?"},{"time":150000,"text":"This is what I found out."},{"time":152000,"text":"I discovered that there's a movement for a better way."},{"time":155000,"text":"Now a while back,"},{"time":157000,"text":"I wanted to be an NFL football player."},{"time":159000,"text":"I decided that I'd rather be an organic farmer instead."},{"time":162000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":171000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":173000,"text":"And that way I can have a greater impact on the world."},{"time":176000,"text":"This man, Joel Salatin, they call him a lunatic farmer"},{"time":179000,"text":"because he grows against the system."},{"time":181000,"text":"Since I'm home-schooled,"},{"time":183000,"text":"I went to go hear him speak one day."},{"time":185000,"text":"This man, this \"lunatic farmer,\""},{"time":187000,"text":"doesn't use any pesticides, herbicides,"},{"time":189000,"text":"or genetically modified seeds."},{"time":192000,"text":"And so for that, he's called crazy by the system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195000,"text":"I want you to know that we can all make a difference"},{"time":198000,"text":"by making different choices,"},{"time":200000,"text":"by buying our food directly from local farmers,"},{"time":202000,"text":"or our neighbors who we know in real life."},{"time":204000,"text":"Some people say organic or local food is more expensive,"},{"time":206000,"text":"but is it really?"},{"time":208000,"text":"With all these things I've been learning about the food system,"},{"time":211000,"text":"it seems to me that we can either pay the farmer,"},{"time":214000,"text":"or we can pay the hospital."},{"time":216000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":223000,"text":"Now I know definitely which one I would choose."},{"time":225000,"text":"I want you to know that there are farms out there --"},{"time":227000,"text":"like Bill Keener in Sequatchie Cove Farm in Tennessee --"},{"time":230000,"text":"whose cows do eat grass"},{"time":232000,"text":"and whose pigs do roll in the mud, just like I thought."},{"time":234000,"text":"Sometimes I go to Bill's farm and volunteer,"},{"time":236000,"text":"so I can see up close and personal"},{"time":238000,"text":"where the meat I eat comes from."},{"time":240000,"text":"I want you to know that I believe"},{"time":242000,"text":"kids will eat fresh vegetables and good food"},{"time":244000,"text":"if they know more about it and where it really comes from."},{"time":247000,"text":"I want you to know that there are farmers' markets"},{"time":249000,"text":"in every community popping up."},{"time":251000,"text":"I want you to know that me, my brother and sister"},{"time":253000,"text":"actually like eating baked kale chips."},{"time":255000,"text":"I try to share this everywhere I go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258000,"text":"Not too long ago,"},{"time":260000,"text":"my uncle said that he offered my six-year-old cousin cereal."},{"time":263000,"text":"He asked him if he wanted organic Toasted O's"},{"time":265000,"text":"or the sugarcoated flakes --"},{"time":267000,"text":"you know, the one with the big striped cartoon character on the front."},{"time":271000,"text":"My little cousin told his dad"},{"time":273000,"text":"that he would rather have the organic Toasted O's cereal"},{"time":275000,"text":"because Birke said he shouldn't eat sparkly cereal."},{"time":279000,"text":"And that, my friends, is how we can make a difference"},{"time":281000,"text":"one kid at a time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"So next time you're at the grocery store, think local,"},{"time":286000,"text":"choose organic, know your farmer and know your food."},{"time":288000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}